Terminology used in support of the data collection efforts of the Clinical Proteomic Tumor Analysis Consortium (CPTAC) with the focus on neoplasms.
This gene is involved in mannose metabolism.
Human GFUS wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 8q24.3 and is approximately 5 kb in length. This allele, which encodes GDP-L-fucose synthase protein, plays a role in GDP-L-fucose synthesis.
GDP-L-fucose synthase (321 aa, ~36 kDa) is encoded by the human GFUS gene. This protein is involved in the NADP-dependent conversion of GDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-D-mannose to GDP-L-fucose.
A treatment plan that specifies the dosage, the schedule, and the duration of treatment.
This gene plays a role in endosome and lysosome transport.

Human CLN3 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 16p12.1 and is approximately 29 kb in length. This allele, which encodes battenin protein, is involved in microtubule-dependent transport of organelles. Deletions within the gene are associated with neuronal ceroid lipofuscinosis type 3 (Batten disease).
Battenin (438 aa, ~48 kDa) is encoded by the human CLN3 gene. This protein plays a role in anterograde transport of late endosomes and lysosomes.
